{"key":"post-14491821","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>14491821</id>\n<content>Disregard that.&amp;nbsp; I found out from the gypsum manufacturer last time I got a truckload that the pelleted gypsum is actually powdered gypsum with a binding agent added to make it easier to spread with machinery.&amp;nbsp; Powdered gypsum would clog up a spreader, but pelleted gypsum rolls right through.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The binding agent is water soluble, so all you need to do is mix it dry with your dry substrate material and when you add water, it will dissolve.&amp;nbsp; There is no need to grind it.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>14491862</next>\n<prev>14491198</prev>\n<first>14490962</first>\n<last>14495097</last>\n<when>1306039099</when>\n<utime>05/22/11 07:38 AM</utime>\n</post>"}